00:00:00:220000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:00:00:220000.Dialogue: All right! I'm moving my infantry division. Augmented by bataillon of orcs from Lord of the Rings. We flank the Tennessee volunteers and the North, once again, wins the battle of Gettysburg.

00:00:12:110000.Speaker: Howard
00:00:12:110000.Dialogue: Not so fast! Remember, the South still has two infantry divisions, plus Superman and Godzilla.

00:00:18:100000.Speaker: Leonard
00:00:18:100000.Dialogue: No, orcs are magic. Superman is vulnerable to magic. Not to mention you already lost Godzilla to the Illinois cavalry and Hulk.

00:00:26:150000.Speaker: Raj
00:00:26:150000.Dialogue: Why don't you just have Robert E. Lee charge the line with Shiva and Ganesh?

00:00:33:000000.Speaker: Howard
00:00:33:000000.Dialogue: Shiva and Ganesh, the Hindu gods, against the entire Union army?

00:00:40:080000.Speaker: Raj
00:00:40:080000.Dialogue: Excuse me. Ganesh is the Remover of Obstacles and Shiva is the Destroyer. When the smoke clears, Abraham Lincoln will be speaking Hindi and drinking mint juleps.

00:00:49:040000.Speaker: Penny
00:00:49:040000.Dialogue: My boss says you have to either order or leave and never come back.

00:00:53:090000.Speaker: Howard
00:00:53:090000.Dialogue: What do you recommend for someone who worked up a man-sized appetite from a morning of weight training and cardio funk?

00:01:00:200000.Speaker: Howard
00:01:00:200000.Dialogue: I'll take the Heart Smart platter.

00:01:03:170000.Speaker: Howard
00:01:03:170000.Dialogue: All right, thank you, and Sheldon?

00:01:05:200000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:01:05:200000.Dialogue: We don't eat here. I don't know what's good.

00:01:11:180000.Speaker: Leonard
00:01:11:180000.Dialogue: Just get a hamburger. You like hamburgers.

00:01:13:210000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:01:13:210000.Dialogue: I like hamburgers where we usually have them. You can't make the assumption that I'll like them here.

00:01:19:030000.Speaker: Leonard
00:01:19:030000.Dialogue: I'm sorry. Give him a hamburger.

00:01:20:090000.Speaker: Penny
00:01:20:090000.Dialogue: Which one? The Classic Burger, the Ranch House Burger, the Barbecue Burger, or the Kobe Burger?

00:01:26:100000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:01:26:100000.Dialogue: Can't we just go to Big Boy? They only have one burger... the Big Boy.

00:01:31:130000.Speaker: Penny
00:01:31:130000.Dialogue: The Barbecue Burger's like the Big Boy.

00:01:33:080000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:01:33:080000.Dialogue: Excuse me, in a world that already includes a Big Boy, why would I settle for something like a Big Boy?

00:01:38:060000.Speaker: Penny
00:01:38:060000.Dialogue: Because you're not at Big Boy!

00:01:44:060000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:01:44:060000.Dialogue: Waitresses don't yell at you at Big Boy.

00:01:50:150000.Speaker: Lesley
00:01:50:150000.Dialogue: I didn't know you ate here.

00:01:52:010000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:01:52:010000.Dialogue: We don't. This is a disturbing aberration.

00:01:54:120000.Speaker: Leonard
00:01:54:120000.Dialogue: Leslie, this is Penny. She lives across the hall from Sheldon and me.

00:01:57:200000.Speaker: Howard
00:01:57:200000.Dialogue: And walks in quiet beauty like the night.

00:02:01:090000.Speaker: Penny
00:02:01:090000.Dialogue: Howard, I've asked you not to do that.

00:02:04:120000.Speaker: Leonard
00:02:04:120000.Dialogue: Leslie and I do research together at the university.

00:02:09:120000.Speaker: Lesley
00:02:09:120000.Dialogue: Yep, come for the breasts, stay for the brains.

00:02:13:070000.Speaker: Lesley
00:02:13:070000.Dialogue: Glad I ran into you. The Physics Department string quartet needs a new cellist.

00:02:18:110000.Speaker: Lesley
00:02:18:110000.Dialogue: He switched over to high-energy radiation research, had a little mishap, and now the other guys are uncomfortable sitting next to him. You're in?

00:02:27:020000.Speaker: Lesley
00:02:27:020000.Dialogue: Great, we rehearse on Tuesdays at your place.

00:02:30:130000.Speaker: Lesley
00:02:30:130000.Dialogue: Department of Energy said our regular space is kind of a hot zone.

00:02:34:150000.Speaker: Penny
00:02:34:150000.Dialogue: Yeah, you, too. I didn't know you played the cello.

00:02:39:050000.Speaker: Leonard
00:02:39:050000.Dialogue: Yeah, my parents felt that naming me Leonard and putting me in Advanced Placement classes wasn't getting me beaten up enough.

00:02:46:150000.Speaker: Howard
00:02:46:150000.Dialogue: If you're into music, I happen to be a human beatbox.

00:02:57:120000.Speaker: Penny
00:02:57:120000.Dialogue: I'm actually not that into music.

00:03:00:120000.Speaker: Penny
00:03:00:120000.Dialogue: Your friend's really cute. Anything going on with you two?

00:03:04:030000.Speaker: Leonard
00:03:04:030000.Dialogue: Leslie? No, no. What, are you kidding?

00:03:06:180000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:03:06:180000.Dialogue: He asked her out once. It was an embarrassing failure.

00:03:15:160000.Speaker: Penny
00:03:15:160000.Dialogue: That's too bad. You guys'd make a cute couple.

00:03:23:120000.Speaker: Howard
00:03:23:120000.Dialogue: How can she take your order when you're too neurotic to talk to her?

00:03:27:080000.Speaker: Raj
00:03:27:080000.Dialogue: Nevertheless, this will be reflected in her tip.

00:03:33:120000.Scene: The stairwell of the apartment building.
00:03:33:120000.Speaker: Leonard
00:03:33:120000.Dialogue: What did Penny mean, You'd make a cute couple?

00:03:36:110000.Scene: The stairwell of the apartment building.
00:03:36:110000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:03:36:110000.Dialogue: I assume she meant the two of you together would constitute a couple that others might consider cute.

00:03:43:060000.Scene: The stairwell of the apartment building.
00:03:43:060000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:03:43:060000.Dialogue: An alternate and somewhat less likely interpretation is that you could manufacture one.

00:03:49:060000.Scene: The stairwell of the apartment building.
00:03:49:060000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:03:49:060000.Dialogue: As in, Look, Leonard and Leslie made Mr. and Mrs. Goldfarb. Aren't they adorable?

00:03:54:130000.Scene: The stairwell of the apartment building.
00:03:54:130000.Speaker: Leonard
00:03:54:130000.Dialogue: If Penny didn't know that Leslie had turned me down, then it would unambiguously mean that she, Penny, thought I should ask her, Leslie, out, indicating that she had no interest in me asking her, Penny, out. But, because she did know that I had asked Leslie out and that she, Leslie, had turned me down, then she, Penny, could be offering consolation.

00:04:13:180000.Scene: The stairwell of the apartment building.
00:04:13:180000.Speaker: Leonard
00:04:13:180000.Dialogue: That's too bad, you would have made a cute couple, but while thinking: Good, Leonard remains available.

00:13:07:010000.Speaker: Lesley
00:13:07:010000.Dialogue: Sorry, I've got to run. If you come up with an adjective, text me.

00:13:14:050000.Scene: The hallway, Sheldon scuttles out of apartment door and crosses to Penny’s. Knocks on it urgently.
00:13:14:050000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:13:14:050000.Dialogue: Inconsiderate. That is the adjective, inconsiderate.

00:13:19:210000.Speaker: Leonard
00:13:19:210000.Dialogue: You can stare at your board all day. She's still going to be right.

00:13:35:220000.Speaker: Penny
00:13:35:220000.Dialogue: Just pretty good? I'd think you were doing very good.

00:13:40:220000.Speaker: Leonard
00:13:40:220000.Dialogue: Pretty, very... there's really no objective scale for delineating variations of good. Why do you ask?

00:13:47:050000.Speaker: Penny
00:13:47:050000.Dialogue: Well, a little bird told me that you and Leslie hooked up last night.

00:13:56:010000.Speaker: Penny
00:13:56:010000.Dialogue: So, is it serious? Do you like her?

00:13:59:020000.Speaker: Leonard
00:13:59:020000.Dialogue: I don't... That's really two different questions. I'm not... Sheldon, we have to go!

00:14:07:230000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:14:07:230000.Dialogue: You're wound awfully tight for a man who's just had sexual intercourse.

00:14:13:150000.Speaker: Penny
00:14:13:150000.Dialogue: All right, I'll talk to you later, but I am so happy for you.

00:14:18:190000.Speaker: Leonard
00:14:18:190000.Dialogue: Thank you. What did she mean she's happy for me? Is she happy that I'm seeing someone? Or is she happy because she thinks that I am? Because anyone who cared for someone would want them to be happy. Even if the reason for their happiness made the first person unhappy.

00:14:37:090000.Speaker: Leonard
00:14:37:090000.Dialogue: Because the second person, though happy, is now romantically unavailable to the first person.

00:14:43:060000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:14:43:060000.Dialogue: Do you realize I may have to share a Nobel Prize with your booty call?

00:14:50:170000.Speaker: Leonard
00:14:50:170000.Dialogue: You know what? I'm being ridiculous. Who cares what Penny thinks? Leslie is a terrific girl. She's attractive. We like each other. She's extremely intelligent...

00:15:07:030000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:15:07:030000.Dialogue: I don't have to believe in it for her to be lucky.

00:15:10:190000.Speaker: Leonard
00:15:10:190000.Dialogue: Regardless, I have a chance at a real relationship with Leslie. I'm not going to pass that up for some hypothetical future of happiness with a woman who may or may not want me to be happy, with a woman who is currently making me happy.

00:15:37:130000.Speaker: Lesley
00:15:37:130000.Dialogue: Careful, Leonard. Liquid nitrogen, 320 degrees below zero.

00:15:49:150000.Speaker: Leonard
00:15:49:150000.Dialogue: Why are you smashing a flash-frozen banana?

00:15:52:070000.Speaker: Lesley
00:15:52:070000.Dialogue: Because I got a bowl of Cheerios and I couldn't find a knife.

00:16:05:220000.Speaker: Leonard
00:16:05:220000.Dialogue: Just extending the intimacy. Do you want to slip over to the radiation lab and share a decontamination shower?

00:16:17:050000.Speaker: Lesley
00:16:17:050000.Dialogue: What exactly do you think's going on between us?

00:16:21:060000.Speaker: Leonard
00:16:21:060000.Dialogue: I'm not sure, but I think I'm about to discover how the banana felt.

00:16:29:060000.Speaker: Lesley
00:16:29:060000.Dialogue: Listen, neither of us are neuroscientists, but we both understand the biochemistry of sex. I mean, dopamine in our brains is released across synapses, causing pleasure. You stick electrodes in a rat's brain, give him an orgasm button, he'll push that thing until he starves to death.

00:16:45:080000.Speaker: Lesley
00:16:45:080000.Dialogue: Well, the only difference between us and the rat is that you can't stick an electrode in our hypothalamus. That's where you come in.

00:16:53:140000.Speaker: Leonard
00:16:53:140000.Dialogue: Yeah, well, I'm just glad to be a part of it.

00:16:59:020000.Speaker: Lesley
00:16:59:020000.Dialogue: I don't know about your sex drive, but I'm probably good till New Year's.

00:17:13:070000.Speaker: Leonard
00:17:13:070000.Dialogue: You want to make plans for New Year's?

00:17:24:150000.Speaker: Howard
00:17:24:150000.Dialogue: The blogosphere is a-buzzin' with news of you and Leslie Winkle making eine kleine bang-bang musik.

00:17:31:120000.Speaker: Leonard
00:17:31:120000.Dialogue: How did it get on the Internet?

00:17:35:110000.Speaker: Leonard
00:17:35:110000.Dialogue: How did you know about it?

00:17:39:230000.Speaker: Raj
00:17:39:230000.Dialogue: Apparently, you are a magnificent beast.

00:17:51:210000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:17:51:210000.Dialogue: I think I may have misjudged this restaurant.

00:17:54:080000.Speaker: Leonard
00:17:54:080000.Dialogue: - No kidding. - I don't want to go out on a limb,

00:18:00:210000.Speaker: Leonard
00:18:00:210000.Dialogue: Your old Tuesday hamburger will be so brokenhearted.

00:18:05:080000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:18:05:080000.Dialogue: Way ahead of you. I was thinking of moving Big Boy to Thursdays, and just dropping Souplantation.

00:18:13:010000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:18:13:010000.Dialogue: The name always confused me anyway. Souplantation. You can't grow soup.

00:18:23:110000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:18:23:110000.Dialogue: Terrific. You'll be happy to know that I plan to come here every Tuesday night for the foreseeable future.

00:18:32:040000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:18:32:040000.Dialogue: Who do I speak to about permanently reserving this table?

00:18:40:050000.Speaker: Penny
00:18:40:050000.Dialogue: So, hey, how are things with you and Leslie?

00:18:45:020000.Speaker: Leonard
00:18:45:020000.Dialogue: To be honest, I don't think it's going to work out.

00:18:49:050000.Speaker: Penny
00:18:49:050000.Dialogue: Oh, that's too bad. Hey, don't worry. I'm sure there's someone out there who's just right for you.

00:18:58:150000.Speaker: Leonard
00:18:58:150000.Dialogue: What did she mean by that?!

00:19:01:110000.Speaker: Leonard
00:19:01:110000.Dialogue: Was that just a generic platitude, or was that a subtle bid for attention?

00:19:07:160000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:19:07:160000.Dialogue: You know why this hamburger surpasses the Big Boy?

00:19:11:100000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:19:11:100000.Dialogue: This is a single-decker hamburger, whereas the Big Boy is a double-decker. This has a much more satisfying meat-to-bun-to-condiment ratio.

00:19:19:100000.Speaker: Leonard
00:19:19:100000.Dialogue: Are you even listening to me?

00:19:21:050000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:19:21:050000.Dialogue: Of course, I'm listening. Blah, blah, hopeless Penny delusion...

00:19:31:040000.Speaker: Leonard
00:19:31:040000.Dialogue: You know, you can grow the ingredients for soup.
